column1: # MASTER DISH LIST v5.1
# 32 dish types scored for Dinneroo prioritisation.
# 23 currently ON Dinneroo | 9 Prospects for recruitment.
# COLUMN DEFINITIONS
# IDENTIFICATION
# rank               Priority order (1 = highest). On-platform dishes ranked by demand
# dish_type          Dish category (e.g. "Indian Curry"
# cuisine            Cuisine classification (e.g. Italian
# on_dinneroo        TRUE = currently on platform | FALSE = prospect for recruitment
# strategic_priority Action classification: Core Driver / Preference Driver / Demand Booster / Deprioritised / Prospect
# PERFORMANCE (how well does it perform where it exists?)
# avg_sales_per_dish Average orders per dish
# pct_zones_top_5    % of zones where this dish ranks in top 5 by sales
# deliveroo_rating   Average star rating (1-5) from customer reviews
# meal_satisfaction  % of customers who liked/loved the meal (post-order survey
# repeat_intent      % of customers who would order again (post-order survey
# OPPORTUNITY (is there unmet demand?)
# dish_suitability   How much value can Dinneroo add? Composite score (1-5) based on:
#                    Familiarity (30%) + Time to cook (25%) + Healthy enough (20%) + Shareable (12.5%) + Customisable (12.5%)
#                    From family behaviour survey (n=404). BLANK if dish not surveyed - NOT penalised.
# open_text_requests Count of explicit REQUEST mentions across all surveys (filtered for "wish"
# wishlist_pct       % who want this dish but don't currently eat it (family behaviour survey
# CONTEXT (informational only - not used in scoring)
# demand_strength    Composite demand score (1.0 = average). Combines avg sales + % zones ranked #1 + % zones top 5.
# consumer_preference Composite preference score (1.0 = average). Combines rating + satisfaction + repeat intent.
# coverage_gap       % of zones where this dish is NOT present. High gap ≠ high opportunity (availability ≠ demand).
# Generated: 2026-01-07 | Version: 5.1
rank
